rComments: Lee is not your average professor. If you need structure, clear grading criteria and availability - she is not the professor for you. She has a lot of offer knowledge wise, is funny and is a great storyteller, but her vagueness/disorganization makes it difficult to do well in her class, in my experience. Not up to U of T standards, IMO.

Lee is one of the most published Indigenous women in Canada. An elder of the Stó:lo nation, Lee is without a doubt one of the most knowledgeable, experienced, and qualified professors at U of T. Her teaching style is based on this experience, and not typical Western academia. Everybody stands to learn a great deal in her presence.

terrible. terrible. terrible. the worst prof i've ever had. 1 sentence comments on marked assignments, or sometimes no comments at all, rude, egotistical, repetitive, scatter-brained, and boring. avoid at all costs!

ENG355H1F Indigenous Women's Literature:  Lee Maracle is amazing! Her lectures are vibrant & memorable. She's direct, but not rude, honest, brilliant, very approachable and helpful. Not an easy A course because she expects a lot from students, and rightly so - she gives way more back than you can ever return. If you want more feedback, just ask her
She has no lesson plans, she is very disorganized and rude, is off topic all the time. he class is so boring. However, it's the easiest A you will ever receive.

She's tough - not afraid of telling it as it is. Class informal and intimate - good for building bonds with other students. She's very open to helping her students, and most importantly, she's passionate about writing. Most work had to be done on our own, but she definitely guides you if you keep your eyes open and you put the work into it. Great!
Disorganized, unprofessional, doesn't show up, loses manuscripts, and verbally abusive.  What's she doing here?

Bullying, disorganised, underqualified. Changed the syllabus at least four times over the course of the year. Lost drafts. Showed up late to class, once not at all. Instead of teaching, talked about whatever came to the top of her head for two hours. Very few comments on student work, ones there completely useless. On the plus side, it's an easy A.
